# JavaScript Execution Environment

## Introduction

A JavaScript Execution Environment is a platform where JavaScript code is executed.
It provides all the necessary components and resources required to run JavaScript programs properly.

JavaScript cannot run directly on the operating system. It needs an execution environment such as:

* Web Browser
* Node.js

The execution environment helps JavaScript:

* Execute code
* Manage memory
* Handle events
* Perform asynchronous operations
* Interact with external systems

---

# Types of JavaScript Execution Environment

## 1. Browser Environment

Browsers are the most common JavaScript execution environments.

Popular browsers:

* Google Chrome
* Mozilla Firefox
* Microsoft Edge
* Safari

Each browser contains a JavaScript engine that executes JavaScript code.

---

## JavaScript Engines in Browsers

| Browser         | JavaScript Engine |
| --------------- | ----------------- |
| Google Chrome   | V8 Engine         |
| Mozilla Firefox | SpiderMonkey      |
| Safari          | JavaScriptCore    |
| Microsoft Edge  | Chakra/V8         |

---

## Features of Browser Environment

* Executes JavaScript inside web pages
* Supports DOM manipulation
* Handles user interactions
* Provides Web APIs
* Supports asynchronous programming

---

## Example of Browser Execution

```html id="y6x5w1"
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h1 id="demo">Hello</h1>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "Welcome to JavaScript";
